# Byte-stability for an integrity repository.
#
# verify.py's sha256 is anchored into every manifest and self-checked at
# runtime; anchor JSON and OpenTimestamps proofs are hashed. A platform
# line-ending rewrite (e.g. a Windows clone with core.autocrlf=true) would
# change those bytes and make verification spuriously fail. Force LF on every
# checkout, and treat .ots proofs as binary so they are never transformed.

* text=auto eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.hex  text eol=lf
*.ots  binary
